# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ⚡ PROBLEM 1-3: Fast Factorial (Recognizing Loop vs Formula)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Problem: For t test cases, compute (n! mod MOD). n up to 10^6, t up to 10^5.
#
# ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
# │                                   🧠 THINKING                             │
# └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

# If you compute n! from scratch each query: O(n) per query → O(n*t) total = TLE.
# Precompute all factorials up to max_n ONCE: O(max_n) preprocessing, O(1) per query.

MOD = 10**9 + 7
MAX_N=10**6+5
fact=[1]*MAX_N
for i in range(1, MAX_N):
    fact[i]=fact[i-1]*i%MOD
#
# Now fact[n] = n! mod MOD in O(1) per query.
#
# ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
# │                                                                          │
# │  KEY TAKEAWAYS                                                           │
# │  ✦  Use sys.stdin.read() + split() — one syscall for all input           │
# │  ✦  Wrap everything in solve() — local variable access is faster         │
# │  ✦  Batch all output into a list, print once at the end                  │
# │  ✦  Bad I/O = TLE on a correct algorithm. Fix I/O first.                 │
# │                                                                          │
# └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
#
# 🎯 ONE LINE:
#   sys.stdin.buffer.read() is 10× faster than input() — always use it in Python CP
#
# 🔍 SIGNALS:
