#   - "how to approach"
#   - "strategy"
#
# ❌ MISTAKES:
#   ✗ Starting with complex algorithm when simple O(n²) passes within time limit
#   ✗ Not checking if brute force is fast enough before optimizing
#
#
# 🧠 THINKING:
#   1. Set up fast I/O with sys.stdin.readline before anything else
#   2. Wrap all logic in solve() — local variables are faster in Python (CPython)
#   3. Match your input-parsing pattern to the problem format (single int, array, grid…)
