# 🧠 THE BIG PICTURE
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Time complexity answers one question: "How much slower does my code get
# as the input gets bigger?"
#
# We write it as O(f(n)) — read "Big-O of f(n)".
# It's a worst-case upper bound that ignores constants and small terms:
#   • O(3n + 7) = O(n)       — constants don't matter at large n
#   • O(n² + n) = O(n²)      — the dominant term wins
#   • O(n log n) is between O(n) and O(n²) — faster than quadratic!
#
