# 💡 PRO TIP:
#   • "Binary search on answer" is one of the most common Div.2 C/D techniques.
# Whenever you see "minimize the maximum" or "maximize the minimum" — think binary search.
#
# • PRO TIP: When writing binary search, always verify your loop condition.
# • "lo < hi" with hi=mid vs "lo <= hi" with lo=mid+1, hi=mid-1.
# • The former finds leftmost feasible; the latter finds exact value.
# • Getting these wrong causes infinite loops on boundary cases.
