# └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
#
#   ✗  Linear scan to find where a value fits in a sorted array: O(n)
#
#   ✓  bisect_left / bisect_right: O(log n) — always use for sorted arrays
#
#   ✗  Binary search with mid = (lo + hi) // 2 bug: infinite loop when lo+1=hi
#       Common pattern: while lo < hi: mid = (lo+hi)//2
#       If predicate(mid) → lo = mid+1, else hi = mid  (or vice versa)
#
#   ✓  Use the FFFTT bisect template below — it is always correct.
#
#   ✗  Forgetting that binary search on answer requires MONOTONE predicate.
#       "Can I achieve result X?" must be monotone: once True, stays True as X grows.
#
#   ✓  Always verify monotonicity before applying "binary search on answer".
#
#   ✗  sorted() inside a loop: O(n² log n) total
#
#   ✓  Sort once before the loop: O(n log n) total
#
# 🎯 ONE LINE:
#   Find first TRUE in monotone FFFTTT sequence — lo moves right, hi moves left, return lo
#
# 🔍 SIGNALS:
#   - "minimum X such that"
#   - "maximum X such that"
#   - "minimum maximum"
#   - "maximum minimum"
#   - "search answer space"
