# ❌ MISTAKES:
#   ✗ Using mid=(lo+hi)//2 when lo+hi overflows (C++ issue, not Python)
#   ✗ Infinite loop: if condition is true, setting hi=mid-1 instead of hi=mid → misses answer
#   ✗ Wrong boundary: lo=0,hi=n when answer could be n → use hi=n+1 or hi=max_possible+1
#   ✗ Not verifying the monotone property — binary search ONLY works on monotone predicates
#
