#   ✓  Heap: push once O(log n), pop-min O(log n)
#
#   ✗  Nested loops for "previous greater element": O(n²)
#
#   ✓  Monotonic stack: single pass O(n)
#       Invariant: stack is always decreasing. When new element arrives,
#       pop everything smaller → those elements' "next greater" is current element.
#
#   ✗  Using list as queue: list.pop(0) is O(n) (shifts all elements)
#
#   ✓  from collections import deque; dq.popleft() is O(1)
#
#   ✗  Python heapq is a min-heap. For max-heap, pushing -x is the trick.
#
#   ✓  heappush(h, -x) to push; -heappop(h) to get max.
#       Or use a wrapper class with __lt__ overridden.
