# └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
#
#   ✗  Generating all subsets of size k with nested for-loops:
#       Becomes unmaintainable for k > 3.
#
#   ✓  itertools.combinations(range(n), k) or recursive backtracking
#
#   ✗  No pruning in backtracking:
#       At each level, trying all choices even when constraint is already violated.
#
#   ✓  Prune EARLY: if current partial solution can never become valid, return immediately.
#       E.g., in N-queens: if column/diagonal is attacked, skip entirely.
#
#   ✗  Recomputing from scratch at each node of the search tree.
#
#   ✓  INCREMENTAL updates: update state, recurse, undo update (backtrack).
#       State is maintained in O(1) per level, not O(n) recomputation.
#
# 🎯 ONE LINE:
#   Backtracking = try → recurse → undo; prune the moment a partial state can't become valid
