# CF TAGS: greedy, arrays  |  Rating: 1000–1400

#
# • PROBLEM 6-2 [Medium]: Minimum Platforms for Train Arrivals/Departures Given
#       arrival and departure times, minimum platforms needed simultaneously
# • Sort arrivals and departures.
# • Two-pointer sweep: count overlapping intervals.
#

# ── min_platforms — inline ──
arrivals.sort()
departures.sort()
count_n=len(arrivals)
platforms=ans=0
j=0
for i in range(count_n):
    platforms+=1
    if platforms>ans:
        ans=platforms
    while j<count_n and departures[j]<arrivals[i]:
        platforms-=1
    j+=1
# result→ans
#
# PROBLEM 6-3 [Medium]: Gas Station
# • Problem: Circular array of gas[i] and cost[i]. Start from some index, go around.
# • Which starting index allows completing the circuit? Greedy: If total gas >= total cost, a solution exists.
# • The starting index is the first position where running total never goes negative.
#

# ── can_complete_circuit — inline ──
if sum(gas)<sum(cost):
    comp_count=-1
else:
    tank=start=0
    for i in range(len(gas)):
        tank+=gas[i]-cost[i]
        if tank<0:
            start=i+1
        tank=0
    comp_count=start
# result→_cc
#
