# 7D. EDIT DISTANCE (Levenshtein) — Classic 2D DP

# Problem: Given strings s and t, find minimum operations (insert, delete, replace)
# to transform s into t.
#
# STATE: dp[i][j] = min operations to transform s[0..i-1] into t[0..j-1].
# BASE CASES:
# • dp[0][j] = j  (insert j characters to get t[0..j-1] from empty)
# • dp[i][0] = i  (delete i characters from s[0..i-1] to get empty)
#
# TRANSITION (transforming s[0..i-1] to t[0..j-1]):
#   If s[i-1] == t[j-1]: no operation needed
# • dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j-1].
#   Else, take minimum of:
#     Replace s[i-1] with t[j-1]: dp[i-1][j-1] + 1
#     Delete s[i-1]: dp[i-1][j] + 1
#     Insert t[j-1] after s[i-1]: dp[i][j-1] + 1
#
# DRY RUN on s="cat", t="hat":
# dp[0] = [0,1,2,3] (insert c,a,t into empty to get "hat")
# dp[1] (s="c"): dp[1][0]=1
# • j=1: s[0]='c',t[0]='h' differ.
# • min(dp[0][0]+1, dp[0][1]+1, dp[1][0]+1) = min(1,2,2)=1
# • j=2: s[0]='c',t[1]='a' differ.
# • min(dp[0][1]+1, dp[0][2]+1, dp[1][1]+1) = min(2,3,2)=2 j=3: s[0]='c',t[2]='t' differ.
# • min(dp[0][2]+1, dp[0][3]+1, dp[1][2]+1) = min(3,4,3)=3.
# dp[2] (s="ca"): ...
# dp[3] (s="cat"): dp[3][3] = 1 (replace 'c' with 'h') ✓
#

# ── edit_distance — inline ──
# result→dp[_m]
#
# 🎯 ONE LINE:
#   Edit distance: dp[i][j] = min ops to convert s[0..i-1] to t[0..j-1] — O(nm).
#
# 🔍 SIGNALS:
#   - "minimum insert/delete/substitute to transform string"
#   - "spell checker", "sequence alignment"
#
# ❌ MISTAKES:
#   ✗ Base case: dp[0][j]=j and dp[i][0]=i (not 0)
#   ✗ Forgetting free match: dp[i][j]=dp[i-1][j-1] when s[i-1]==t[j-1]
#   ✗ Not using rolling array when memory is tight
#
# 🧠 THINKING:
#   1. Match: free. Mismatch: take min of insert, delete, substitute (+1 each).
#   2. dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j-1] if match, else 1+min(dp[i-1][j], dp[i][j-1], dp[i-1][j-1]).
#
