#
# 🎯 ONE LINE:
#   Two pointers on sorted array: converge from both ends — O(n) after sort.
#
# 🔍 SIGNALS:
#   - "find pair with given sum in sorted array"
#   - "count pairs with sum < / > / = k"
#
# ❌ MISTAKES:
#   ✗ O(n²) nested loops when sorted → two pointers is O(n)
#   ✗ Not sorting first — two pointers requires sorted input
#
# 🧠 THINKING:
#   1. lo at left, hi at right. Sum too small: lo++. Too large: hi--.
#   2. O(n) single pass.
