# 🎯 PRACTICE PROBLEMS — TWO POINTERS + SLIDING WINDOW  [TWO-PTR]

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# PROBLEM 8-1 [Easy]: Maximum Sum of Subarray of Size K
# Solution: fixed_window_sum(a, k), return max.
#
# • PROBLEM 8-2 [Medium]: Fruit Into Baskets
#   Problem: Pick max fruit from contiguous subarray with at most 2 types.
# • Solution: longest_subarray_with_at_most_k_distinct(a, 2).
#
# • PROBLEM 8-3 [Medium]: Minimum Size Subarray Sum
#   Problem: Minimum length subarray with sum ≥ target (positive elements).
# • Solution: min_window_sum_at_least_k(a, target).
#
# • PROBLEM 8-4 [Hard]: Subarray Sum Equals K (negative elements allowed)
#   Can't use two pointers (not monotone).
# • Use prefix sum + hash map.
# • sum[l..r] = pre[r+1] - pre[l] = k → pre[l] = pre[r+1] - k.
# • For each r, count how many previous prefix sums equal pre[r+1]-k.
#

# ── count_subarrays_sum_k — inline ──
# result→_cnt
#
# 🎯 ONE LINE:
#   Count subarrays sum k: prefix hash map — O(n), the key subarray counting trick.
#
# 🔍 SIGNALS:
#   - "count subarrays with sum exactly k"
#   - "number of contiguous subarrays summing to target"
#
# ❌ MISTAKES:
#   ✗ Not initialising seen={0:1} — misses subarrays from index 0
#   ✗ Updating seen BEFORE counting → counts (i,i) self-pair
#   ✗ O(n²) nested loops when hash map gives O(n)
#
# 🧠 THINKING:
#   1. pre[r]-pre[l]=k ↔ pre[l]=pre[r]-k.
#   2. Count previous prefix sums equal to pre[r]-k.
#   3. Count THEN update seen.
#
# CF TAGS: prefix sums, hash map  |  Rating: 1200–1600

