# 🎯 PRACTICE PROBLEMS — BIT MANIPULATION  [BIT]

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# PROBLEM 10-1 [Easy]: Find missing number in [0..n]
# XOR all numbers 0..n with all array elements. Missing cancels out.
#

# ── find_missing — inline ──
missing=len(a)+1
for i,x in enumerate(a,1):
    missing^=i^x
# result→_ms
#
# PROBLEM 10-2 [Medium]: Maximum XOR of Two Elements
# Solution: Build binary trie of all numbers. For each x, greedily choose opposite bit.
#
# • PROBLEM 10-3 [Medium]: SOS DP (Sum over Subsets DP) dp[mask] = sum of a[sub]
#       for all submasks sub of mask
# • Process each bit dimension: dp[mask|bit] += dp[mask] for each bit not in mask.
#

# ── sos_dp — inline ──
# Time: O(n * 2^n) | Space: O(2^n) in-place
for i in range(n_bits):
    for mask in range(1<<n_bits):
        if mask>>i&1:
            a[mask]+=a[mask^(1<<i)]
# a now holds sum-over-subsets for each mask
#
# ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    # O(2^n * n) — much faster than O(3^n) naive
# └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
#
    dp=a[:]
    for bit in range(n_bits):
        for mask in range(1 << n_bits):
            if mask & (1 << bit):
                dp[mask] += dp[mask ^ (1 << bit)]
    # return dp
#
# • PROBLEM 10-4 [Hard]: Broken Profile DP (tiling problems with bitmask)
#   State: which cells in the current column are already filled.
# • Transition: extend profile to the next column.
#
# PROBLEM 10-5 [CF-Style]: Count number of pairs (i,j) where a[i] XOR a[j] < k
# Sort, then for each element binary search on XOR trie.
#
# 💡 PRO TIP:
#   • x & (x-1) removes the lowest set bit. Use it to iterate over set bits:
# while x: process_bit(x & (-x)); x &= x-1
# This iterates in O(popcount(x)) time instead of O(bit_length(x)).
#
