# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ⚠️ EDGE CASE CHECKLIST
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   □  source = target: distance = 0 immediately
#   □  Unreachable nodes: dist[v] = INF (don't print INF, print -1 if problem asks)
#   □  Multiple edges between same pair: Dijkstra handles naturally (takes min)
#   □  n=1: no edges, dist[1] = 0, all others = INF
#   □  Dijkstra stale entry: MUST check if d > dist[u] before processing
#   □  Floyd-Warshall: loop order k, i, j — NOT i, j, k (breaks DP correctness)
#   □  Self-loops with positive weight: no impact on shortest paths
#
