# ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
# └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
#
#   ✗  Naive LCA: climb from both nodes up to root alternately: O(n) per query
#
#   ✓  Binary lifting LCA: O(n log n) preprocessing, O(log n) per query
#       up[v][k] = 2^k-th ancestor of v. To find LCA(u,v): equalize depths, then jump.
#
#   ✗  Recomputing subtree sums from scratch for each query: O(n) per query
#
#   ✓  Euler tour flattens tree: subtree(u) maps to contiguous array segment.
#       Use BIT for O(log n) range updates and point queries.
#
#   ✗  Tree DP without considering rerooting:
#       "dp[u] = answer when u is root" requires ALL nodes as root.
#
#   ✓  Rerooting (re-rooting DP): compute dp[u] bottom-up, then compute
#       dp2[u] top-down using dp2[parent] + contribution adjustment.
#
# 🎯 ONE LINE:
#   Tree diameter = two BFS: farthest from any node, then farthest from that — always O(n)
