#   → Ch12 — Kruskal's MST processes edges sorted by weight; Union-Find checks cycles
#   → Ch13 — Prim's is Dijkstra on edge weights; both produce MST on same graph
#   → Ch18 — Link-Cut Tree extends DSU to support dynamic graph connectivity#
# ⛔ ANTI-PATTERNS (wrong algorithm for wrong situation)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   ✗ Union-Find on a directed graph for reachability → DSU only models
#       undirected connectivity. FIX: use DFS/BFS or SCC for directed graphs.
#   ✗ Using DSU to detect cycles in a directed graph → misses directed cycles.
#       FIX: use topological sort (Kahn's); cycle ↔ not all nodes processed.
#   ✗ Forgetting path compression → O(n) per find in worst case instead of O(α).
#       FIX: always compress (path halving or full compression).
#   ✗ Kruskal on a directed graph → MST is only defined on undirected graphs.
#       FIX: for directed MST use Edmonds' (Chu-Liu) algorithm.

