#
#   ✗  BFS/DFS to check connectivity for each edge in Kruskal: O(n) per edge → O(mn) total
#
#   ✓  DSU: check connectivity in O(α(n)) ≈ O(1). Kruskal becomes O(m log m) total.
#
#   ✗  Prim with adjacency list + naive O(n) scan for minimum: O(n²)
#
#   ✓  Prim with heap: O((n+m) log n) — better for sparse graphs
#       For dense graphs (m ≈ n²): matrix Prim O(n²) is often faster in practice.
#
#   ✗  "MST of subgraph with k nodes" via running full Kruskal: wastes edges
#
#   ✓  Kruskal stops when n-1 edges added. Still sort all m edges. O(m log m).
#
# 🎯 ONE LINE:
#   Kruskal: sort all edges then DSU; Prim: grow from one node with heap — both O(m log m)
#
