# HLD COMMON MISTAKES:
# 1. Forgetting to process the heavy child LAST in DFS so positions are contiguous.
# 2. Edge weights vs node weights — for edge weights, assign to the lower node.
# 3. LCA finding — HLD gives LCA at no extra cost (when head[u] == head[v]).
# 4. Centroid decomp: always reset removed[] between problems.
# 5. Small-to-large: set union in Python is O(|smaller|) — make sure you merge right.
