# ⚠️ EDGE CASE CHECKLIST
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   □  No path from s to t → max flow = 0.
#   □  Capacity = 0 on some edges → should not be augmented (check cap > 0).
#   □  Multiple edges between same pair of nodes → allowed, just add all of them.
#   □  Source = sink → undefined; problem guarantees s ≠ t usually.
#   □  Node capacities: split each node v → v_in and v_out with edge cap=node_cap.
#   □  Bipartite: add super-source connected to all left nodes, super-sink from all right.
#   □  Integer capacities → integer max flow (max flow theorem).
