# GEOMETRY COMMON MISTAKES:
# 1. Float precision: use integer arithmetic (cross products) whenever possible.
#    For float: always use EPS = 1e-9 comparisons. Never ==.
# 2. Convex hull with collinear points: decide upfront whether to include them.
# 3. Cross product sign depends on orientation (CW vs CCW convention).
# 4. Segment vs line: intersection of LINES may not be on the SEGMENTS.
# 5. Degenerate cases: 0, 1, 2 points in "convex hull."
