# 🧠 HOW TO THINK — PATTERN RECOGNITION SIGNALS
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
#   ► "smallest convex polygon containing all points"         → convex hull
#
#   ► "do two line segments intersect?"                       → cross product test
#
#   ► "area of a polygon given vertices"                      → shoelace formula
#
#   ► "point inside or outside polygon"                       → ray casting
#
#   ► "closest pair of points"                                → divide & conquer O(n log n)
#
#   ► "k-th nearest, range queries on 2D points"              → KD-tree (rare in CP)
#
#   ► "maximize linear function over convex hull"             → convex hull trick (Ch7/DP)

