#
#   ✗  Using floating point for all geometry → precision errors accumulate.
#
#   ✓  Use integer arithmetic wherever possible. Cross product with integers = exact.
#       For angles/distances requiring floats: add epsilon (1e-9) for comparisons.
#
#   ✗  Computing convex hull with O(n²) gift-wrapping (Jarvis march) for n > 10^4.
#
#   ✓  Graham scan or Andrew's monotone chain: O(n log n). Use for n > 1000.
#
#   ✗  Forgetting to handle collinear points in convex hull.
#       Some problems want collinear points included, others excluded.
#
#   ✓  Check problem statement: "strictly convex" = no collinear. Use >= vs > accordingly.
#
# 🎯 ONE LINE:
#   Cross product sign gives turn direction: >0 left turn, <0 right turn, =0 collinear — convex hull core
#
# 🔍 SIGNALS:
