# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# □  Collinear points: cross product = 0. Most algorithms assume non-collinear.
# □  Coincident points: distance = 0. Guard all divisions by distance.
# □  Degenerate polygon: 0, 1, or 2 points — handle before general code.
# □  Orientation: ensure CCW. Use: if polygon_signed_area(pts) < 0: pts.reverse()
# □  Integer coords: use integer cross products for exact results (no EPS needed).
# □  Large coords: cross of 10^9-scale → 10^18 — Python int handles this exactly.
# □  Point exactly on boundary: ray casting may misclassify. Check separately.
# □  Parallel lines: line_intersection_geo returns None. Always handle this case.
