# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ⚠️ EDGE CASE CHECKLIST
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   □  n=1: phi(1)=1, has no prime factors, is not prime.
#   □  p=2: only even prime. Sieve starts from 2.
#   □  Large n (10^12+): need Miller-Rabin, not trial division.
#   □  MOD itself: (MOD % MOD = 0) — answer could be 0, that's valid.
#   □  Division in modular arithmetic: a/b mod p = a * pow(b, p-2, p) only when p is prime.
#   □  Overflow: Python handles big integers natively, but other languages need care.
#   □  gcd(0, n) = n — handle n=0 edge case in GCD function.
