# 🧠 MENTAL MODEL
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
#   "Matrix exponentiation = compress k steps of a linear recurrence into O(log k)."
#   Any linear recurrence f(n) = c1*f(n-1) + c2*f(n-2) + ... → matrix form.
#   [[f(n+1)], [f(n)]] = M * [[f(n)], [f(n-1)]] → M^n * [[f(1)], [f(0)]]
#   Key: if the transition is LINEAR and CONSTANT, it can be a matrix.
#
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 🧠 HOW TO THINK — PATTERN RECOGNITION SIGNALS
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
#   ► "compute f(n) for n up to 10^18"                        → matrix exponentiation
#
#   ► "linear recurrence of order k (k small)"                → k×k matrix
#
#   ► "count paths of length exactly k in a graph"            → A^k (adjacency matrix)
#
#   ► "Fibonacci, tribonacci, or custom linear recurrence"    → matrix expo
#
#   ► "tile a 2×n grid with dominoes"                         → profile DP → matrix expo
#
#   ► "transition function that doesn't change with time"     → matrix expo candidate

# ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
# └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
#
#   ✗  Computing Fibonacci(10^18) with memoized recursion.
#       O(n) time and space — impossible for n=10^18.
#
#   ✓  Matrix exponentiation: [[F(n+1)],[F(n)]] = [[1,1],[1,0]]^n * [[1],[0]]
#       O(k³ log n) where k=2 → O(8 log n) ≈ instant for n=10^18.
#
#   ✗  Building full n×n matrix when only a k×k transition matrix is needed.
#       Common confusion: graph has n nodes, but recurrence has order k << n.
#
#   ✓  Matrix size = recurrence order (k), not graph size.
#       For "paths of length k in graph": matrix is n×n adjacency matrix.
#       For "k-th term of recurrence": matrix is order×order.
#
# 🎯 ONE LINE:
#   Matrix size = recurrence order k, NOT graph size n — common confusion causes TLE
#
# 🔍 SIGNALS:
#   - "how to approach"
#   - "strategy"
#
