# ── compute_grundy — inline ──
# result→grundy
#
# 🎯 ONE LINE:
#   Grundy values: MEX of reachable states — combine independent games with XOR.
#
# 🔍 SIGNALS:
#   - "arbitrary impartial game"
#   - "game on DAG of states"
#   - "sum of independent games"
#
# ❌ MISTAKES:
#   ✗ Computing MEX wrong (must be min excludant — smallest non-negative int NOT in set)
#   ✗ Forgetting Grundy(0)=0 (terminal state, no moves)
#   ✗ XOR only works for SUM of INDEPENDENT games
#
# 🧠 THINKING:
#   1. Grundy(state) = MEX({Grundy(next) for each move}).
#   2. XOR of Grundy values across independent sub-games = Grundy of combined game.
#
# CF TAGS: game theory, math  |  Rating: 1600–2200

#
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ▶ EXAMPLE: Subtraction game with moves {1, 3, 4}
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# G = compute_grundy([1,3,4], 20)
# → G[0]=0, G[1]=1, G[2]=0, G[3]=1, G[4]=2, G[5]=3, G[6]=2, G[7]=0, ...
# Pattern repeats with period 7 for this move set.
#

# ── compound_game_winner — inline ──
# sub_game_states=list of state ints; moves_per_game=list of move sets; max_n=max state
grundy_nums=[[0]*(max_n+1) for _ in range(len(sub_game_states))]
for gcd_val,moves in enumerate(moves_per_game):
    for i in range(1,max_n+1):
        reachable=set()
        for m in moves:
            if i-m>=0:
                reachable.add(grundy_nums[gcd_val][i-m])
        mex_val=0
        while mex_val in reachable:
            mex_val+=1
        grundy_nums[gcd_val][i]=mex_val
xor_val=0
for gcd_val,state in enumerate(sub_game_states):
    xor_val^=grundy_nums[gcd_val][state]
compound_wins=(xor_val!=0)
# result→_cgw (True=first player wins)
#
# STAIRCASE NIM: Piles on stairs 0,1,...,n. Can move any stones from stair k
# to stair k-1. Stair 0 is the "ground." First to clear all stairs wins.
#
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ▶ KEY INSIGHT: Only ODD-indexed stairs matter!
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# XOR of pile sizes on ODD stairs determines winner.
# (Moving to even stair: opponent can mirror move to stair below. Irrelevant.)
#

# ── staircase_nim_winner — inline ──
xor_val=0
for i in range(1,len(stairs),2):
    xor_val^=stairs[i]
stair_wins=(xor_val!=0)
# result→_sn_win
#
# MISÈRE: Last player to move LOSES (reverse of normal play).
# For NIM specifically (and only NIM):
#   If all piles ≤ 1: win if and only if the number of piles is even.
#   Otherwise:        win if and only if XOR ≠ 0 (same as normal NIM!).
# This is NOT generally true for other games.
#

# ── misere_nim_winner — inline ──
xor_val=0
for prime in piles:
    xor_val^=prime
all_one=all(prime<=1 for prime in piles)
misere_wins=(xor_val==0 if all_one else xor_val!=0)
# result→_mn_win
