# ║                      BONUS G — MANACHER'S ALGORITHM                      ║
# ╚════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

# WHAT: Finds, for every center position (character or gap between characters),
#   the radius of the longest palindrome centered there — in O(n) total.
#   Output: array p[] where p[i] = radius of longest palindrome centered at i.
#
# 💡 KEY INSIGHT:
#   • THE Z-BOX ANALOGY:
# • Maintain [l, r]: the rightmost palindrome interval found so far.
# • For position i inside [l,r]: mirror i around center → i' = l+r-i.
# • p[i] ≥ min(p[i'], r-i) — use mirror, then try to extend.
# • When i > r: extend naively from scratch.
# • The right boundary r only moves rightward → O(n) total extensions.
#
# IMPLEMENTATION (odd-length palindromes):
#
# def manacher_odd(s):
#     n = len(s)
#     p = [0] * n          # p[i] = radius of palindrome at i (0 = single char)
#     l, r = 0, -1
#     for i in range(n):
#         k = 1 if i > r else min(p[l + r - i], r - i)
#         while i - k >= 0 and i + k < n and s[i-k] == s[i+k]:
#             k += 1
#         p[i] = k - 1
#         if i + k - 1 > r:
#             l, r = i - k + 1, i + k - 1
#     return p
#
# EVEN-LENGTH: transform s → s' by inserting '#' between every character:
#   "abba" → "#a#b#b#a#".  Run manacher_odd on s'.  Recover even palindromes.
#   Alternatively, maintain two arrays (p_odd, p_even) with two passes.
#
# ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
# │                                 🚀 APPLICATIONS                           │
# └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

#   • Longest palindromic substring: max(p[i]) over all i → O(n).
#   • Count palindromic substrings:  sum(p[i] + 1) for odd + similar for even.
#   • Palindrome at position [l..r]: check p[center] ≥ (r-l)//2.
#   • Palindromic partitioning DP:   precompute p[], then DP in O(n) or O(n log n).
#
# KEY PROBLEMS:
#   CF 5E   — Shortest Palindrome                        [1900]
#   CF 906E — Mirror Box                                 [2700]  palindromic structure
#   CF 1063H — Palindrome Shuffle                        [2800]  see Ch26 training plan
#   Leetcode 5 — Longest Palindromic Substring  (warm-up)
#
# TRAINING:
#   DAY 1: Implement manacher_odd. Verify p[] on "aaabaaaa" → [0,1,2,0,3,0,1,0].
#   DAY 2: Add even-palindrome support via '#'-insertion trick.
#   DAY 3: Solve CF 5E (build shortest palindrome using Manacher + KMP).
#   GOAL:  "palindrome query on string" → Manacher in < 5 min implementation.
#
