# ║                       BONUS H — SQRT DECOMPOSITION                       ║
# ╚════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

# • WHAT: Divide an array of n elements into blocks of size B ≈ √n.
# • Precompute per-block summaries.
# • Answer range queries in O(B + n/B) = O(√n) by combining full blocks + partial left/right endpoints.
# • With B = √n, both update and query are O(√n).
# • Simple, no recursion.
#
# WHEN TO USE:
#   • Segment tree would work but you need "lazy with two different lazy types" →
#     sqrt decomp is simpler to implement under contest pressure.
#   • Online queries that don't fit offline-only methods (Mo's).
#   • "Sqrt trick" for optimizing O(n²) DP → split into heavy/light by size ≥ √n.
#
