# ▶ THE 20 MOST COMMON CF BUGS (with fixes)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

#  1. Off-by-one: range(n) vs range(1,n+1).
#     FIX: 1-indexed arrays with size n+2 buffer.
#
#  2. Segment tree wrong size: n vs 4*n.
#     FIX: Always allocate 4*n nodes.
#
#  3. BIT is 1-indexed internally.
#     FIX: Shift all user indices by +1 when accessing the BIT.
#
#  4. Uninitialized distance: dist[start] should be 0, not INF.
#     FIX: dist=[INF]*(n+1); dist[start]=0.
#
#  5. Dijkstra on negative edges → silent wrong answer.
#     FIX: Use Bellman-Ford / SPFA for negative weights.
#
#  6. Visited / dp arrays not reset between test cases.
#     FIX: Move ALL initialization INSIDE the test case loop.
#
#  7. Recursion depth on chain-shaped tree n=10^5.
#     FIX: Iterative DFS with explicit stack.
#
#  8. Union-Find without path compression: O(n) per query.
#     FIX: Always use path compression AND union by rank.
#
#  9. Modular arithmetic: forgot to mod before multiply.
#     FIX: Apply %MOD after every + and * in the hot path.
#
# 10. Graph edge direction: only u->v for undirected.
#     FIX: adj[u].append(v); adj[v].append(u).
#
# 11. Prefix sum off-by-one: range [l,r] = pre[r+1]-pre[l].
#     FIX: Choose one convention, comment it, never deviate.
#
# 12. heapq is MIN-heap: for max-heap push -x.
#     FIX: heapq.heappush(h,-x); answer=-heapq.heappop(h).
#
# 13. Multiple test cases, global state not reset.
#     FIX: Every mutable structure re-initialized inside test case loop.
#
# 14. dp[i-1] at i=0 → Python wraps to dp[-1].
#     FIX: Use 1-indexed DP arrays or explicit if i>0 guard.
#
# 15. Float comparison: a==b.
#     FIX: abs(a-b) < 1e-9. Never == on floats.
#
# 16. Output format: "YES"/"NO" vs "Yes"/"No" vs "yes"/"no".
#     FIX: Re-read the problem output section before every submit.
#
# 17. Binary search lo/hi boundary for "first true" vs "last false".
