# ⚠️ EDGE CASE CHECKLIST
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#   □  Empty string: KMP/Z should return [] (no matches, z=[0]).
#   □  Pattern longer than text: no matches possible.
#   □  All same characters: "aaaa" — Z-array, KMP failure have special patterns.
#   □  Hashing: separator '#' must not appear in text/pattern.
#   □  Hash collision: use double hashing for safety in competitive setting.
#   □  Suffix array: strings with identical characters — sorting stability matters.
#   □  Unicode: ord() works for Python strings, but stick to ASCII for CP.
