# FFT: polynomial multiplication in O(n log n) using complex roots of unity.
# NTT: same but over a prime modulus (998244353 = 119·2²³+1 supports NTT).
#      Use NTT when answers must be taken mod a prime.
#

# ── ntt — inline ──
# NTT implementation — keep for reference; use only with MOD=998244353
# Cooley-Tukey butterfly in-place: standard O(n log n) NTT
