# ▶ 29G. STRESS TESTING FRAMEWORK
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# • Stress testing: run BRUTE FORCE vs OPTIMIZED on random small inputs.
# • When they disagree → you found a failing test case.
# • This catches: wrong answers, off-by-ones, edge cases, TLE on small n.
#
# STRUCTURE:
#   generator()   → random small test case
#   brute(input)  → correct but slow O(n²) or O(n³) solution
#   fast(input)   → your optimized solution
#   compare and print first mismatch
#
import random
#

# ── stress_test — inline ──
# stress_test — compare brute vs fast on random inputs
