# Before submitting, run through this checklist:
#
# INPUT/OUTPUT:
# □ Read ALL inputs (don't leave any unread)
# □ Output format matches exactly (spaces, newlines, YES/NO case)
# □ Multiple test cases: reset all mutable state between cases
#
# ARRAY/INDEX:
# □ 0-indexed vs 1-indexed arrays (pick one, be consistent)
# □ Array size: n+1 if you need indices 1..n
# □ Off-by-one in loops: range(n) = [0,n-1]; range(1,n+1) = [1,n]
# □ BIT/Segtree: node count is 4*n, not 2*n
#
# OVERFLOW:
# □ Python integers don't overflow, but intermediate values in modular
#   arithmetic can be huge — apply % MOD at each multiplication
# □ float: 1e18 has precision issues; use integers where possible
#
# GRAPH:
# □ Is graph 0-indexed or 1-indexed?
# □ Is it directed or undirected?
# □ Are edge weights in the right field of your tuple?
# □ Dijkstra: initialize dist[source]=0, all others=INF
#
# DP:
# □ Base cases correct?
# □ Iteration order correct (are future states accessed before computed)?
# □ Correct initial value (0 for counting, INF for minimizing, -INF for max)?
# □ For 2D DP: is (i,j) order right or should it be (j,i)?
#
# EDGE CASES TO ALWAYS TEST:
# □ n = 1 (single element)
# □ All elements identical
# □ Already sorted / reverse sorted
# □ Empty input / empty graph
# □ Disconnected graph
# □ n = 0 (if allowed by constraints)

